        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position place="head" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>If there be any coniuring; woold not A rowt troupe of Diuels, make [the] brauist harte in [the] world to guake, &amp; to
                        pisse for feare?
                    </marginalia_text>
                    <emphasis method="pen" type="straight" text="troupe"/>
                </position>
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>If [Michael - deleted]</marginalia_text>
                </position>
                <position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Ismael</marginalia_text>
                    <!-- CG: Possibly 'Ismail Mirza', founder of the Sufi dynasty? https://books.google.com/books?id=ijk5AAAAMAAJ&q=ismael+mursa&dq=ismael+mursa&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CCUQ6AEwAGoVChMInpGAjLuIyAIVglY-Ch0_UA3k --> 
                    <!--KS: I think so too, Ismail was himself even sometimes decribed as a 'thunderbolt launched by the Almighty'-->
                </position>
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Mursa, cowld command thunderbolts &amp;tempests or if Doctor Faustus cowld reare Castels, &amp;
                    arme Diuels at pleasure: What woenderful, &amp; monstrous exploits might be acheuid by</marginalia_text>
                    <person name="Doctor Faustus"/>
                    <person name="Ismael Mursa"/>
                </position>
                <position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>such terrible meanes?</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Embushments,</marginalia_text>
                </position>
                <position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Camisados,</marginalia_text>
                </position>
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>&amp; such pore shifes, but trifles,</marginalia_text>
                </position>
                <position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>in comparison</marginalia_text>
                </position>
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>of [the] cunning</marginalia_text>
                </position>
                <position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>practises, &amp;</marginalia_text>
                </position>
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>horrible furyes, that Diuel cowld play.</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
